# Sunrise Budget — Project Context

Next.js 16 budget app with end-to-end encryption. Tech: React 19, TypeScript, Zustand, Tailwind, shadcn/ui, react-hook-form, Zod, Vitest.

## Structure

- `src/app/` — Routes and API
- `src/components/budget/` — Budget UI; always export new components from `index.ts`
- `src/store/` — Zustand state (budget.ts, session.ts)
- `src/lib/` — Pure utilities (no React, no store): crypto, constants, schedule-format, schedule-builders, import-normalizers
- `src/hooks/` — Derived data and shared UI logic

## Conventions

- New constants/labels → `lib/constants.ts`
- Schedule formatting → `lib/schedule-format.ts`
- Form-to-model logic → `lib/schedule-builders.ts` or new lib module
- New budget UI → `components/budget/` + add to `index.ts`

## Security

Budget data is encrypted. Never log plaintext or expose decrypted data in UI or error messages.
